Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.67,0:19:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,happens is the downside of our animal\Nnature gets repressed
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.91,0:19:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when it gets repressed it gets projected\Nonto others or
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.76,0:19:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,projected against our self-hatred.\NSo later on we'll talk about the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.79,0:19:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,dualities the levels of consciousness\Nwhich is the book we just finished and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.48,0:19:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,um we've been presenting that at\Nlectures you know because each of levels
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.79,0:19:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness has attractions and it\Nhas aversions you know
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.40,0:19:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so we recapitulate the evolution of\Nconsciousness throughout all of time
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.28,0:19:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and there we see that the the emergence\Nof life which is unique
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.36,0:20:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,solely possible via divinity.\NThe emergence of life then in its
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.03,0:20:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,earliest form we calibrated as protozoa\Nat calibration level one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.84,0:20:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The emergence of animal life is you do\Nnot have within yourself the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.20,0:20:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,necessary for your own survival.\NWhen you understand that, you end up
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.72,0:20:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,with compassion for all of\Nlife because animal life is created
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.15,0:20:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,deficient. You're deficient the second\Nyou're born. Without your mother's milk,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.91,0:20:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you will soon die. Therefore, we're\Ncreated as deficient and needy. So, the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.03,0:20:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,core of the ego is neediness.\NIt must always get energy from out
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.20,0:20:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,there.\Nin the primitive form. Then this emerged
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.52,0:21:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,as some way of sampling your\Nenvironment. Is this edible or not
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.20,0:21:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,edible? Is this compatible, not\Ncompatible? Is this friend or foe? So
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.36,0:21:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencer is like a information\Nprobe. the advancing edge of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.84,0:21:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,which we eventually identify as I and\Nget stuck with it as a self-defin
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.40,0:21:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which puts us in duality but the animal\Nside then for eons
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.36,0:21:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the law it's law of survival is to get\Nto be able to overcome that is extremely
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.32,0:21:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,rare in society. Yeah, we say that\Nto be able to get beyond the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.15,0:21:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,cravingness, the fixation of the solar\Nplexus of wantingness
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.76,0:21:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it gets transformed into\Nsymbolic forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.28,0:22:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Survival now is having a lot of money or\Nbig car, wealthy,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.32,0:22:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,having an education,\Nhaving political power. So it gets
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.55,0:22:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,transformed into symbols. But the innate\Ndriving this is still the same power
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.84,0:22:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,over others. You see now why anybody in\Ntheir right mind would want power over
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.79,0:22:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,others is beyond me. But\Nit activates a lot of people's
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.08,0:22:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness to have power over others.\NAs you can see the capacity for power
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.67,0:22:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,within the self with a capital S is\Ninfinite. Once you realize that any
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.60,0:22:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,offers of power are very unattractive.\NI can remember it coming to me one time
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.03,0:22:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,having transcended just about\Neverything. There was nothing left and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.12,0:22:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the silence came a knowingness.\NUm a temptation apparently one of the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.60,0:23:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,great temptations. It says all power is\Nyours now. Own it. And I thought, for
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.55,0:23:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,what?\NAnd so I turned it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.36,0:23:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you're not answerable, now you\Nrealize that you're beyond personal
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.12,0:23:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,karma. All power is yours. Because you\Nsee, love is a limitation. If you're
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.08,0:23:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,going to exploit people, isn't it? It's\Neasy to throw them out on the street. If
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.48,0:23:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not capable of love, it's hard to\Nthrow them out on the street. I would
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.79,0:23:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,hate to be a slum lord. to be in moral\Nagony all the time. You know what I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.28,0:23:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,saying?\NYou can't afford the rent anymore. Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.64,0:23:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it's out, old lady.\NYou're on your own, Granny.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.60,0:23:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Pack your bags and get.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.79,0:23:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing that everything is merely the\Nemergence of its own potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.44,0:24:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When the conditions are appropriate,\Nthen you realize that intention is the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.40,0:24:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,empowerment that enables manifestation\Nto occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.44,0:24:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is held in mind tends to\Nmanifest. The higher the level of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.44,0:24:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness,\Nthe more that is. So
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.24,0:24:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,people of a high consciousness, if you\Nhold a thing even for a few minutes or
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.40,0:24:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,seconds actually in mind, it will tend\Nto manifest in your life. And therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.91,0:24:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the wise um watch what it is that they\Nhold in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.24,0:24:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll need the that we'll need the\Nthings. Yeah. What you hold in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.08,0:24:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to manifest. Huh. That's a\Nreality. And the greater
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.76,0:24:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,why because the Heisenberg principle you\Nsee says that merely observing a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.32,0:24:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,phenomena already changes it.\NWhat the Heisenberg principle doesn't go
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.32,0:25:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,into is the power of the level of\Nconsciousness of the observer.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.55,0:25:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They were talking about scientists\Nprobably in the mid 400s
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.24,0:25:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,uh astute scientists maybe around 450\N460 that's astute science
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.20,0:25:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,when they look at it it changes the\Noutcome what would happen with if
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.15,0:25:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody at a 600 looked at it or 550 or\Nsomething it would be even more likely
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.60,0:25:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to manifest. Yes. All right. So for\Nthose who haven't been here before,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.40,0:25:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to quickly recapitulate\Nthe levels of consciousness. Yeah. And
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.72,0:25:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,keep in mind these all have to be\Ntranscended. If you want to reach
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.91,0:25:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,serenity,\Nyou have to get up early in the morning
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.15,0:25:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and work on it all day long.\NYou may not have serenity, but you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.36,0:25:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,have exhaustion. So you'll sleep.\NThis of course is extremely well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.24,0:26:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I see uh Noetic Sciences or\Nsomebody Omega Institute's going to have
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.36,0:26:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,an conference on maps of consciousness\Nin Reinbeck pretty soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.03,0:26:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, maps of consciousness are\Nnow therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.20,0:26:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,uh considered rather important. Why?\Nbecause it it's the open sesame to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.52,0:26:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,realizing the truth of just about\Neverything that is
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.55,0:26:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that there is such a thing.\NSee, mankind has never known truth from
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.55,0:26:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,falsehood, never had any capacity.\NAnd usually what is substituted is
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.08,0:26:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,persuasion, persuasion. And then of\Ncourse the long came the intellect and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.55,0:26:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you had some kind of academic proof. But\Nwe had no way of discerning truth from
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.76,0:26:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,falsehood. So as a result of the\Nevolution of consciousness of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.67,0:26:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,uh a means of discerning truth from\Nfalsehood appeared uh within the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.03,0:27:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness of somebody in the planet\Nwho then uh wrote about it so others
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.08,0:27:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,would know about it etc. Because such a\Ngift is not you know yours to hoard and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.24,0:27:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,uh and keep secret but to share w with\Nthe world for whatever benefit may
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.55,0:27:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,occur. every advance in in knowledge uh\Nhas a a beneficial fallout
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.32,0:27:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes known and sometimes completely\Nunknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.15,0:27:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, what we discovered was\Nuh in watching kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.55,0:27:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,uh is that it was not a local phenomena\Nof this causing of that. On the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.20,0:27:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,contrary, it was a response of the\Ninfinite field of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.84,0:27:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to the presentation of a stimulus\Nand the response was equivalent to the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.08,0:27:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,strength of the stimulus. Therefore, we\Nended up a gradation from 1 to a,000
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.76,0:28:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,logarithmic and discovered that anything\Nover 200 was true and everything below
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.91,0:28:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,200 was false. So, we ended up with a\Nrelative scale. Okay. So kinesi
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.03,0:28:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology then was a clinical was\Nclinical science not academic science.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.79,0:28:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Academic science\Nis limited to the 400s. Clinical science
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.64,0:28:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,starts really at 500.\Nacademic science.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.03,0:28:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That difference between a clinician who\Ncalibrates over 500 and 100 is quite
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.12,0:28:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,remarkable\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.96,0:28:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,uh my witnessing because I had the huge\Nclinic back east. Some doctors got
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.00,0:28:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,tremendous results with just about\Neverybody even the most impossible cases
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.12,0:28:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and other doctors who are academically\Nequally well trained uh got relatively
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.36,0:28:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,comparatively miserable results. So the\Nenergy of the healer, the healingness
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.44,0:29:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,then comes out of intention and the\Nintention of caring for your patient and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.20,0:29:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing them as well and being dedicated\Nto them is why some doctors have rather
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.91,0:29:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,uh incredible practices. Uhhuh.\NIntention.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.52,0:29:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are the levels of consciousness\Nand we calibrated them. They're pretty
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.67,0:29:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,much traditional throughout man's\Nhistory. uh the alignment in in Columbia
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.91,0:29:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Psychoanalytic these were called the\Nemergency emotions and these are the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.03,0:29:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,welfare emotions. These are the ones\Nthat bring you in to see the doctor and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.52,0:29:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,these are the ones that take take you\Nout.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.67,0:29:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I never saw any patients who suffered\Nfrom serenity. Never did.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.20,0:29:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, their problem was they were\Nallergic to serenity. You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.03,0:30:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,serenity is the last thing. A lot of\Npeople don't like serenity. And although
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.60,0:30:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a you know we consider it an axiom\Nin the in spiritual evolution serenity
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.76,0:30:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,frankly is not uh sought by large\Npercentage of the population probably
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.27,0:30:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the majority majority of the population\Nuh really is not interested in serenity
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.44,0:30:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because if they have the option they\Nturn it down all the time. They turn it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.76,0:30:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,down all the time. They pick an\Nargument. The TV shows are full of blood
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.27,0:30:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and murder.\Nand conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.55,0:30:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So how to uh reach a state of serenity\Nin a sort of chaotic appearing world you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.55,0:30:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,see because people of all different\Nlevels of consciousness and animal life
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.08,0:30:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,etc. is all thrown in together. I mean\Num to get along here with people who are
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.20,0:30:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,just like that uh is a snap right? hang\Nout with people that calibrate 350. Your
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.44,0:31:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,life is joyful. They're cheerful,\Nhelpful, they volunteer, the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.32,0:31:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,humanitarian.\NSo if everybody was right here at 350,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.76,0:31:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, this would be a great place.\NSerenity would be sort of automatic
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.20,0:31:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence.\NNo, what's happened is that in the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.52,0:31:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,world, you know, 80% or so, 80% are\Nbelow the level of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.44,0:31:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,below this level. So, we're living in a\Nworld uh sort of like the bottom of the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.32,0:31:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,sea. There lots of sharks and octopuses\Nand people out to get you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.44,0:31:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and the butterfly flesh are up here. I\Ndon't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.51,0:31:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. But but that's why it's\Nmaximum karmic benefit because we have
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.60,0:31:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the an infinite series of choices\Nbecause we can undo negative karma and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.64,0:32:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,gain positive karma. Uh this is a great\Nbenefit. The Buddhist said how fortunate
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.36,0:32:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to be born a human. How rare to be born\Na human. You think of all living things
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.64,0:32:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the chances of being born a human is\Nminut minuscule
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.20,0:32:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,0.00 something.\NAnd then to be spiritually aligned on
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.32,0:32:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,top of that is rarer still. And to\Nchoose to strive for enlightenment is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.00,0:32:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the rarest of all. Rarest of all.\NPractically never happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.03,0:32:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we calibrated um the desire for\Nenlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.44,0:32:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,uh occurs in less than one in 10 million\Npersons
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.79,0:32:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,less than one in 10 million persons if\Nyou ask them say what's your greatest
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.24,0:32:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,ambition to achieve in your lifetime\Nwould say enlightenment you so
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.67,0:32:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,consequently it has been rare over time\Nyou know
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.08,0:32:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,all right so we've got this calibrated\Nscale now I just want to say something
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.84,0:32:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,about turn off the light a second about\Nkinesiiality ology and the place of it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.91,0:33:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in research. Yeah, it's a research tool.\NThe Institute for Consciousness Research
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.64,0:33:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is based on uh the research done using\Nkinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.15,0:33:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, kinesiology is just like a tool,\Nyou know, it's like a thermometer or
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.39,0:33:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,something. You're not supposed to\Ngenulect in front of the thermometer.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.67,0:33:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a it's just a handy rough\Ntool, you know, not perfected. It's not
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.88,0:33:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the ultimate,\Nbut it's quick and handy. Uhhuh. Uh you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.36,0:33:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,don't uh you know go through a computer\Nto decide what you're going to have for
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.39,0:33:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,lunch. Just say, "Well, I'll have that.\NMy cholesterol is maybe a little high.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.24,0:33:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lot of fish." I mean, that's not\Na great big deal. You know what I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.36,0:33:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,saying? So, you don't have to make a big\Ndeal out of kinesiology. It was useful
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.60,0:33:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in research.\NThen I made the mistake of sharing it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.51,0:33:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,with the world.\NWell, the mistake I made in the first
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.60,0:34:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,book, Harvest is forest, I presumed that\Neverybody could do kinesiology, you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.48,0:34:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,know, with relative ease or relative\Naccuracy and then discovered later that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.91,0:34:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it's only people who calibrate 200 and\Nover. Oh dear, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.24,0:34:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And in America, 49% of the population\Ncalibrates below 200. So there goes 50%.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.56,0:34:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I found out about 10% people for\Nsome karmic reason are unable to do it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.52,0:34:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you know. Then on top of that your\Nmotivation has to be integrous. Uh you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.67,0:34:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,have to have two integrous people who\Nboth calibrate over 200 and and it can't
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.80,0:34:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,be saved as a question. It's it's made\Nas a statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.67,0:34:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh so\Nto be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.96,0:34:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,pose a detached scientific question that\Nis also rare. So
